## Search Engines

## search operators:
- "exact phrase" - looking for exact words on page
- site: - looking for something on exact site'
- - (minus sign) - omit search results with phrase that I don't want in my search
- filetype: - for example pdf, ppt, doc etc.

## Examples
site:github.com password
filetype:ppt "drones in sourveying"

## Conclusions
Using search operators helps you find specific data and makes it easier to search for sensitive data or system documentation, for example.
